%2C%20we%20continue%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20Fed's%20tightening%20cycle%20is%20complete.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20noted%20in%20the%20FOMC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fmediacenter%2Ffiles%2FFOMCpresconf20231101.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epress%20conference%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20staff%20did%20not%20put%20a%20recession%20back%20in%26quot%3B%20the%20forecast%20as%20recent%20activity%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20really%20indicative%20of%20a%20recession%20in%20the%20near%20term.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20slowing%20wage%20growth%2C%20workers%20may%20finally%20be%20seeing%20their%20earnings%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20big%20spike%20in%20inflation.%20Year-over-year%20changes%20from%20BLS%20show%20there%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Frealer.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereal%20wage%20growth%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20based%20on%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20outpacing%20CPI%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there's%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20for%20workers%20to%20fully%20regain%20their%20buying%20power.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPollak%20noted%20recent%20data%20that%20showed%20%26quot%3Ba%20decline%20in%20real%20disposable%20income%2C%20which%20suggests%20that%20consumer%20spending%20may%20come%20under%20pressure%20in%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20which%20would%20further%20cool%20the%20labor%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Bunker%2C%20economic%20research%20director%20for%20North%20America%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Braises%20are%20great%2C%20but%20if%20they%20don't%20get%20you%20any%20more%20purchasing%20power%26quot%3B%20that's%20not%20ideal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20at%20least%20for%20now%2C%20wages%20are%20growing%20more%20quickly%20than%20inflation%2C%20