3EThe%20commercial%20juggernaut%20seems%20unstoppable%2C%20so%20it%E2%80%99s%20perhaps%20easy%20to%20be%20cynical%20about%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%E2%80%9D%20song%20from%20a%20band%20that%20broke%20up%20in%201970%2C%20two%20of%20whose%20members%20are%20dead.%20Certainly%2C%20%E2%80%98Now%20and%20Then%E2%80%99%20does%20raise%20questions%20about%20how%20technologically%20mediated%20releases%20relate%20to%20collective%20artistic%20output%2C%20and%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20a%20band.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECollective%20creativity%20in%20bands%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20though%2C%20the%20AI%20label%20is%20a%20red%20herring%2C%20and%20this%20new%20song%20%E2%80%93%20which%20actually%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20a%20John%20Lennon%20demo%20tape%20from%201977%20%E2%80%93%20demonstrates%20a%20continuing%20pattern.%20The%20Beatles%20and%20their%20narrative%20provided%20a%20seminal%20example%20of%20how%20bands%20work%2C%20and%20seemed%20to%20be%20ploughing%20the%20furrow%20for%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20their%20original%20formation%20as%20schoolboys%20(Ringo%20joined%20in%201962%20when%20they%20started%20recording)%2C%20to%20their%20enormous%20financial%20success%20and%20cultural%20impact%2C%20the%20Beatles%20laid%20down%20templates%20that%20others%20have%20followed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.liverpoolecho.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fnostalgia%2Fjuly-6-1957-day-beatles-9594637%5C%22%3ELennon%20and%20McCartney%E2%80%99s%20first%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20church%20fete%20in%201957%20is%20now%20the%20stuff%20of%20legend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-beatles-revolutionised-music-by-putting-the-record-centre-stage-56103%5C%22%3Einnovations%20in%20the%20studio%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20assisted%20by%20producer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FGeorge-Martin%5C%22%3EGeorge%20Martin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20helped%20to%20make%20recordings%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20albums%20%E2%80%93%20a%20central%20feature%20of%20the%20popular%20music%20experience.%20They%20emerged%20into%20professional%20practice%20together%2C%20splitting%20as%20they%20formed%20new%20relationships%20and%20moved%20onto%20the%20next%20phases%20of%20their%20life%20while%20still%20relatively%20young%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBands%20are%20simultaneously%20social%20groupings%2C%20creative%20units%20and%20economic%20entities.%20The%20economic%20%E2%80%9Cbrand%E2%80%9D%20can%20obviously%20run%20on%20for%20many%20years%20after%20the%20others%20have%20stopped.%20There%20is%20also%20long%20history%20of%20posthumous%20releases%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.loudersound.com%2Ffeatures%2Fjimi-hendrix-6-essential-posthumous-albums%5C%22%3EJimi%20Hendrix%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fmusic%2Freviews%2F6fmq%2F%5C%22%3EElliott%20Smith%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprince-why-five-years-after-his-death-the-purple-one-still-reigns-159166%5C%22%3EPrince%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20Otis%20Redding%E2%80%99s%20defining%20hit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rollingstone.com%2Fmusic%2Fmusic-features%2Finside-otis-reddings-final-masterpiece-sittin-on-the-dock-of-the-bay-122170%2F%5C%22%3E(Sittin%E2%80%99%20On)%20The%20Dock%20of%20the%20Bay%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Demo%20recordings%2C%20unheard%20live%20performances%20and%20radio%20broadcasts%20are%20all%20established%20parts%20of%20artists%E2%80%99%20catalogues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20becomes%20complicated%2C%20though%2C%20when%20the%20act%20in%20question%20is%20a%20collective%20with%20deceased%20members%20whose%20presence%20on%20the%20recording%20is%20technologically%20facilitated.%20A%20key%20example%20is%20the%20Beatles%201995%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fultimateclassicrock.com%2Fbeatles-free-as-a-bird%2F%5C%22%3EAnthology%3C%2Fa%3E%20project%2C%20which%20saw%20the%20surviving%20members%20revisit%20John%20Lennon%20demos%20from%20a%20cassette%20given%20to%20McCartney%20by%20Yoko%20Ono%2C%20and%20add%20new%20parts%20to%20finish%20the%20songs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20entirely%20unique.%20Queen%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.udiscovermusic.com%2Fbehind-the-albums%2Fqueen-made-in-heaven%2F%5C%22%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20same%20year%2C%20saw%20the%20band%20finish%20songs%20that%20Freddie%20Mercury%20worked%20on%20in%20the%20studio%20before%20he%20died.%20But%20it%20did%20involve%20resurrecting%20fragments%20of%20home%20recordings%20to%20clean%20them%20up%20for%20the%20commercial%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20sufficient%20at%20the%20time%20to%20properly%20isolate%20Lennon%E2%80%99s%20voice%20on%20%E2%80%98Now%20and%20Then%E2%80%99%2C%20so%20it%20was%20abandoned%20until%20Peter%20Jackson%20used%20machine%20learning%20to%20remove%20noise%20from%20source%20recordings%20for%20%E2%80%98Get%20Back%E2%80%99.%20By%20this%20time%20George%20Harrison%20had%20died%2C%20so%20this%20technology%20allowed%20McCartney%20and%20Starr%20to%20return%20to%20the%20song%2C%20incorporating%20Harrison%E2%80%99s%20guitar%20solo%20from%20the%20aborted%201990s%20attempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECome%20together%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20can%2C%20then%2C%20consider%20the%20process%20behind%20this%20latest%20song%20in%20evolutionary%20rather%20than%20revolutionary%20terms.%20The%20possibilities%20of%20multi-track%20recording%20since%20the%201950s%20mean%20it%E2%80%99s%20long%20been%20the%20case%20that%20musicians%20have%20worked%20separately%20on%20the%20same%20song.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theneweuropean.co.uk%2Fbrexit-news-the-beatles-white-album-60s-70s-john-lennon-wider-cultural-35006%2F%5C%22%3EGeorge%20Harrison%20said%20of%20The%20White%20Album%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20lot%20more%20individual%20stuff%20%E2%80%A6%20people%20were%20accepting%20that%20it%20was%20individual.%20I%20remember%20having%20three%20studios%20operating%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20Paul%20was%20doing%20some%20overdubs%20in%20one%2C%20John%20was%20in%20another%20and%20I%20was%20recording%20some%20horns%20or%20something%20in%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20the%20Beatles%20were%20together%2C%20many%20canonical%20songs%20were%20the%20work%20of%20only%20one%20or%20two%20of%20them.%20McCartney%20wrote%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DwXTJBr9tt8Q%5C%22%3EYesterday%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DMan4Xw8Xypo%5C%22%3EBlackbird%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%20alone%2C%20and%20is%20the%20only%20Beatle%20who%20plays%20on%20them.%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dv-1OgNqBkVE%5C%22%3EThe%20Ballad%20of%20John%20and%20Yok%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%20didn%E2%80%99t%20feature%20Harrison%20or%20Starr.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20former%20band%20members%20played%20on%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csolo%E2%80%9D%20records%20too.%20There%20are%20more%20Beatles%20on%20Harrison%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DeNL40ql4CYk%5C%22%3EAll%20Those%20Years%20Ago%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20Lennon%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D7-SSa-D1i-M%5C%22%3EInstant%20Karma%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20on%20some%20of%20the%20band%E2%80%99s%20tracks.%20They%20all%20played%20separately%20on%20Starr%E2%80%99s%201973%20album%20Ringo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20%E2%80%98Now%20and%20Then%E2%80%99%20continues%20longstanding%20practices%2C%20going%20back%20to%20their%20heyday.%20Its%20status%20as%20the%20final%20Beatles%20song%2C%20though%2C%20reveals%20technological%20limitations.%20AI%20can%20create%20convincing%20facsimiles%2C%20but%20can%E2%80%99t%20replicate%20the%20facts%20of%20who