ticleshow%2F105093878.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20husband%20was%20forced%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office.%20Life%20got%20harder%20and%20more%20expensive%20when%20all%20of%20the%20parenting%20duties%20fell%20to%20me.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223171%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20family%20with%20two%20sons%20takes%20a%20photo%20on%20a%20cliff%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a9f52b788914e5551ffe4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222378%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarquita%20and%20Jaime%20Wright%20with%20their%20sons%2C%20Jaimeson%20and%20Marley.%3Cp%3EHannah%20McFall%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20Marquita%20Wright%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20working%20from%20home%2C%20they%20split%20childcare%20duties.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20had%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20full%20time.%20Now%20Wright%20takes%20care%20of%20their%20twin%20sons'%20transportation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20use%20babysitters%20to%20help%20free%20up%20some%20time%2C%20but%20it%20costs%20them%20about%20%24200%20a%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Marquita%20Wright%2C%20a%2039-year-old%20business-development%20manager%20and%20travel%20blogger%20in%20New%20Orleans.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20in%20business%20development%20for%20a%20conveyor%20manufacturer%2C%20and%20my%20husband%2C%20Jaime%2C%20is%20a%20civil%20engineer%20for%20the%20federal%20government.%20I've%20been%20working%20from%20home%20full%20time%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20was%20working%20from%20home%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20too.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20have%20twin%20boys%2C%20Jaimeson%20and%20Marley%2C%20who%20are%20now%205.%20When%20the%20pandemic%20began%2C%20they%20were%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20my%20husband%20around%20made%20it%20a%20lot%20easier%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20lot%20more%20fun.%20We%20shared%20all%20the%20parenting%20duties%20fairly%20equally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThen%20my%20husband%20went%20back%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2018%20months%20ago%2C%20he%20was%20told%20he%20had%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20three%20days%20per%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20going%20back%20to%20the%20office%20meant%20we%20needed%20to%20reconsider%20how%20to%20balance%20our%20work%20and%20family%20life.%20It%20also%20meant%20a%20lot%20more%20work%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20work%20isn't%20as%20flexible%20as%20we%20hoped.%20They%20asked%20why%20he%20needed%20to%20run%20on%20a%20certain%20schedule.%20I%20work%20full%20time%20as%20well%2C%20but%20my%20workplace%20is%20more%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20his%20job%20were%20more%20flexible%2C%20he'd%20be%20able%20to%20help%20me%20with%20school%20drop-offs%20and%20pickups%2C%20as%20well%20as%20homework%2C%20weekly%20play-therapy%20appointments%2C%20and%20other%20after-school%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20twins%20starting%20school%20changed%20our%20schedule%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20twins%20started%20pre-K.%20We%20chose%20to%20have%20them%20go%20to%20two%20separate%20schools%20because%20they%20learn%20very%20differently.%20The%20one%20who's%20very%20academically%20inclined%20goes%20to%20a%20Catholic%20school%2C%20and%20the%20other's%20at%20a%20Waldorf%20school%2C%20which%20has%20a%20different%20education%20style%20centered%20around%20arts%20and%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20curriculums%20are%20totally%20opposite.%20They%20love%20it%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20separation%20is%20good%20for%20them.%20Neither%20of%20them%20have%20had%20any%20complaints%20about%20wanting%20to%20go%20to%20the%20same%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChoosing%20the%20right%20schools%20for%20our%20boys%20meant%20more%20work%20for%20us%2C%20but%20that's%20OK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20organize%20pickup%20and%20drop-off%20days%20around%20the%20days%20my%20husband%20was%20going%20into%20the%20office%3A%20I%20would%20pick%20them%20up%20and%20drop%20them%20off%20when%20he%20had%20to%20go%20in%2C%20and%20the%20days%20he%20worked%20from%20home%20he%20would%20take%20on%20the%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20husband's%20schedule%20changed%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20ago%2C%20my%20husband%20was%20told%20he%20had%20to%20start%20going%20into%20the%20office%20every%20day.%20This%20meant%20he%20could%20no%20longer%20do%20the%20drop-off%20two%20days%20a%20week%20and%20it%20was%20all%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Waldorf%20school%20doesn't%20start%20until%208%3A30%20a.m.%2C%20and%20because%20my%20husband%20has%20to%20be%20at%20work%20by%209%20a.m.%2C%20it%20just%20isn't%20possible%20for%20him%20to%20do%20the%20drop-off%20if%20he%20wants%20to%20make%20it%20on%20time%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20isn't%20finished%20with%20work%20in%20time%20to%20pick%20them%20up%20when%20school%20closes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESchool%20drop-offs%20and%20pickups%20take%20hours%20each%20day%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20spend%20anywhere%20from%203%20to%204%20%C2%BD%20hours%20every%20day%20doing%20school%20drop-offs%20and%20pickups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20accomplish%20what%20I%20need%20to%20get%20done%20for%20my%20job%2C%20but%20it%20means%20I%20need%20to%20wake%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20start%20making%20lunches%20at%206%3A45%20a.m.%20I%20then%20do%20school%20drop-offs.%20I%20normally%20can't%20get%20back%20into%20my%20work%20until%208%3A45%20a.m.%20Then%20I%20usually%20have%20to%20stop%20work%20at%204%3A45%20p.m.%20so%20I%20can%20pick%20them%20up%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20start%20and%20finish%20my%20day%20by%20spending%20at%20least%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20on%20school%20runs.%20If%20there's%20play%20therapy%2C%20which%20one%20of%20the%20boys%20goes%20to%20after%20school%20some%20days%2C%20that's%20an%20extra%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20kids'%20getting%20sick%20or%20having%20appointments%20also%20means%20I%20need%20to%20step%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20schools%20call%2C%20or%20if%20we%20have%20to%20go%20to%20the%20doctor%2C%20I'm%20now%20the%20only%20parent%20who%20can%20pick%20them%20up.%20It%20makes%20our%20life%20a%20lot%20more%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20time%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20together%20alone%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20is%20also%20now%20even%20more%20limited.%20After%20the%20boys%20are%20asleep%2C%20I'm%20heading%20to%20bed%20so%20I%20can%20rest%20for%20my%205%20a.m.%20wake-up%20call%2C%20leaving%20us%20only%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20catch%20up%20and%20prepare%20for%20the%20upcoming%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20use%20babysitters%2C%20but%20they're%20costly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20from%20Milwaukee%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20is%20from%20Miami%2C%20so%20we%20don't%20have%20a%20family%20support%20network%20here%20in%20New%20Orleans%20to%20help%20us%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20couple%20of%20sitters%20we%20use%20regularly%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20about%20twice%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20whom%20we%20found%20on%20Care.com.%20We%20spend%20around%20%24200%20per%20week%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sitters%20help%20with%20school%20pick-up%20and%20will%20often%20take%20the%20boys%20to%20the%20park%20to%20burn%20off%20their%20energy%20before%20coming%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20help%20for%20a%20few%20days%20allows%20us%20both%20to%20pursue%20our%20hobbies%20outside%20of%20work.%20For%20me%20that's%20working%20on%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marquitastravels.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etravel%20blog%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20flips%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20prefer%20working%20from%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20happy%20that%20I%20have%20the%20flexibility%20to%20work%20from%20home.%20I%20wish%20my%20husband%20could%20return%20to%20working%20from%20home%20a%20few%20days%20a%20week%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20look%20like%20that%20will%20happen%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20is%20on%20a%20hybrid%20schedule%2C%20I%20have%20the%20flexibility%20to%20work%20in%20silence%20without%20interruption%20on%20the%20days%20he's%20at%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20then%20on%20the%20days%20he's%20at%20home%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20adjust%20my%20schedule%20to%20drop%20off%20and%20pick%20up%20the%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-returning-to-office-more-work-me-spend-money-childcare-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699524601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654aa2473cc84b4dfafe23f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-returning-to-office-more-work-me-spend-money-childcare-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Marquita%20Wright%20works%20full%20time%20from%20home%20and%20spends%20anywhere%20from%203%20to%204%20%C2%BD%20hours%20every%20day%20doing%20school%20drop-offs%20and%20pickups.%20Their%20childcare%20costs%20have%20also%20risen%20to%20%24200%20a%20week.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Elle%20Hardy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-returning-to-office-more-work-me-spend-money-childcare-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parineeti%20vacays%20with%20mom%20and%20mother-in-law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699524442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105093715%2Cimgsize-36880.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fparineeti-chopra-enjoys-her-vacation-in