om-hiddleston-zawe-ashton-to-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone-celebrity-couples-who-worked-together-in-film-franchises%2Fphotostory%2F105088389.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Has%20Maximum%20Cases%20Of%20Tuberculosis%20In%20The%20World%3A%20WHO%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20Tuberculosis%20(TB)%20cases%20in%20the%20world%20in%202022%2C%20says%20the%20Global%20TB%20Report%202023%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation.%20The%20country%20accounted%20for%2027%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20total%20TB%20cases%20in%20the%20world.%20There%20were%2028.2%20lakh%20cases%20and%20of%20them%2C%2012%20per%20cent%20(3%2C42%2C000%20people)%20died%20due%20to%20the%20disease%2C%20said%20the%20report%2C%20which%20was%20released%20on%20Tuesday.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-src%3D%5C%22visualisation%2F15677891%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20Global%20Burden%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20revealed%20that%2030%20nations%20accounted%20for%2087%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20world's%20TB%20cases.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20followed%20by%20Indonesia%20(10%20per%20cent)%2C%20China%20(7.1%20per%20cent)%2C%20the%20Philippines%20(7.0%20per%20cent)%2C%20Pakistan%20(5.7%20per%20cent)%2C%20Nigeria%20(4.5%20per%20cent)%2C%20Bangladesh%20(3.6%20per%20cent)%2C%20and%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%20(3.0%20per%20cent).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-src%3D%5C%22visualisation%2F15666698%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20shows%20India%20has%20made%20progress%20in%20reducing%20the%20number%20of%20cases.%20From%20258%20patients%20per%201%2C00%2C000%20people%20in%202015%2C%20it%20has%20dropped%20to%20199%20per%201%2C00%2C000%20people%20in%202022.%20But%20the%20rate%20is%20still%20far%20higher%20than%20the%20global%20average%20of%20133%20per%20100%2C000.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-src%3D%5C%22visualisation%2F15666792%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ECase%20Fatality%20Ratio%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECase%20Fertility%20Ratio%20(CFR)%20--%20the%20measure%20of%20how%20severe%20a%20disease%20is%20--%20of%20India%20stood%20at%2012%20per%20cent%2C%20which%20means%2012%20out%20of%20100%20patients%20died%20of%20the%20disease.%20%C2%A0The%20figure%20is%20the%20double%20of%20the%20global%20average%20which%20stands%20at%205.8%20per%20cent.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingapore%20had%20the%20lowest%20score%20of%201%20per%20cent%20while%20China%20stood%20at%2014th%20spot%20with%204%20per%20cent.%20While%20TB%20is%20curable%2C%20death%20can%20occur%20when%20it%20is%20diagnosed%20late.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-src%3D%5C%22visualisation%2F15667144%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20has%20made%20matters%20worse%20is%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20estimated%20that%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20number%20of%20deaths%20spiralled.%20Compared%20to%20pre-pandemic%20trends%2C%20around%2060%2C000%20more%20people%20died%20in%20India%20between%202020%20and%202022.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20more%20than%2075%20lakh%20people%20from%20192%20countries%20were%20diagnosed%20with%20TB%20in%202022%2C%20marking%20it%20the%20highest%20figure%20recorded%20since%20WHO%20began%20monitoring%20the%20disease%20across%20the%20world%20from%201995.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%C2%A0A%20Silver%20Lining%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20highlights%20a%20recovery%20trend%20in%20TB%20diagnosis%20and%20treatment%20services%20in%202022%2C%20signalling%20a%20potential%20reversal%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20impact%20on%20TB%20control%20efforts.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699512840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.