%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fothers%2Fcmo-is-a-hub-of-corruption-pm-modi-targets-baghel-govt-in-chhattisgarh-101699354711084.html%5C%22%3Ehub%20of%20corruption%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20Singhvi%20objected%20to%20Modi%20pronouncing%20Baghel%20guilty.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20this%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98level%20playing%20field%E2%80%99%20issue.%20The%20level%20playing%20field%20directly%20impinges%20on%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20on%20democracy%20and%20therefore%2C%20violates%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20free%20ration%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20refraining%20from%20petitioning%20the%20poll%20body%20over%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20of%20a%20free%20ration%20scheme%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20continued%20to%20step%20up%20its%20attack.%20Congress%20leader%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20was%20the%20same%20prime%20minister%20who%20called%20such%20welfare%20measures%20by%20Congress%20as%20%E2%80%9Crevidis%20(freebies)%E2%80%9D%20is%20now%20declaring%20his%20free%20ration%20scheme%20as%20a%20social%20upliftment%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20poll-bound%20Chattisgarh%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20Saturday%2C%20November%204%2C%20had%20said%20his%20government%20will%20extend%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Anna%20Yojana%2C%20which%20provides%205%20kg%20of%20free%20food%20rations%20every%20month%20to%20about%2080%20crore%20poor%2C%20by%20another%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20rolled%20out%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20free%20ration%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20is%20going%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20December%2C%20but%20it%20will%20be%20extended%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years.%20This%20is%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20guarantee%20that%20the%20stoves%20will%20keep%20burning%20in%20the%20homes%20of%20my%2080%20crore%20countrymen%2C%E2%80%9D%20Modi%20said%20while%20addressing%20a%20rally%20in%20Durg%20in%20Chhattisgarh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20Congress%20called%20out%20Modi%20for%20violating%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20(MCC)%20by%20making%20new%20announcements%2C%20Modi%20told%20crowds%20at%20his%20campaigns%20that%20Congress%20is%20against%20free%20ration%20to%20the%20poor.%20%E2%80%9CLet%20them%20commit%20this%20sin%2C%20I%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20good%20work%20for%20the%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Fmadhya-pradesh-assembly%2Fcongress-wants-to-complain-to-ec-over-free-ration-scheme-extension-let-them-commit-this-sin-pm-modi%2Farticle67512325.ece%3Fcx_testId%3D39%26cx_testVariant%3Dcx_1%26cx_artPos%3D3%26cx_experienceId%3DEXT8TLE3MA2V%23cxrecs_s%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20addressing%20a%20public%20meeting%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Damoh%20town.%20%E2%80%9CEighty%20crore%20people%20will%20get%20free%20ration%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699512606000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09112839%2FThe-Wire-71.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-moves-election-commission-against-misuse-of-ed-in-chhattisgarh-rajasthan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20party%2C%20however%2C%20has%20not%20petitioned%20the%20poll%20body%20against%20the%20free%20ration%20scheme%20announced%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20despite%20indicating%20earlier%20that%20it%20amounted%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20poll%20code%20and%20vowed%20to%20raise%20the%20issue%20with%20EC.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-moves-election-commission-against-misuse-of-ed-in-chhattisgarh-rajasthan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Improves%20in%20Tuberculosis%20Detection%20but%20Misses%20Major%20Death%2C%20Incidence%20Milestones%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09115911%2F4903953427_9db86dcdff_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Global%20Tuberculosis%20Report%202023%2C%20issued%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%2C%20offered%20a%20mixed%20bag%20for%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20India%20improved%20case%20detection%20for%20TB%20and%20was%20able%20to%20cover%20the%20losses%20made%20during%20the%20pandemic%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20it%20missed%20major%20milestones.%20India%2C%20incidentally%2C%20accounts%20for%20the%20highest%20TB%20burden%20across%20the%20world%20contributing%2027%25%20of%20all%20the%20TB%20cases%20followed%20by%20Indonesia%20(10%25)%20and%20China%20(7.1%25).%20The%20current%20report%20of%202023%20gives%20figures%20on%20various%20indicators%20of%20TB%20for%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20any%20country%E2%80%99s%20TB%20elimination%20programme%2C%20a%20major%20challenge%20is%20not%20to%20miss%20the%20cases%20and%20see%20to%20it%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20cases%20are%20registered%20or%20%E2%80%98notified%E2%80%99.%20A%20patient%20getting%20missed%20is%20not%20only%20harmful%20for%20the%20individual%20concerned%20but%20also%20her%20contacts%20as%20she%20might%20transmit%20the%20TB%20infection%20to%20them.%20So%20the%20governments%20across%20the%20world%20try%20to%20increase%20notification%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20cases%20every%20year%20and%20close%20the%20gap%20between%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eestimated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20TB%20incidence%20and%20vis-a-vis%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eactually%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20newly%20notified.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20WHO%20report%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20the%20Philippines%2C%20which%20collectively%20accounted%20for%20a%20large%20share%20of%20the%20global%20reductions%20in%20the%20notification%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enewly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20diagnosed%20cases%20in%202020%20and%202021%20(the%20two%20pandemic%20years)%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20them%20recovered%20to%20above%202019%20levels%20(pre-pandemic%20stage)%20in%20the%20year%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20three%20countries%20themselves%20had%20reported%20losses%20in%20notification%20in%20the%20two%20pandemic%20years%20to%20the%20tune%20of%2060%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetail.aspx%3FPRID%3D1975724%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20Union%20health%20ministry%20on%20the%20evening%20of%C2%A0%20November%208%20also%20pointed%20out%20the%20%E2%80%98achievement%E2%80%99%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20%5BIndia%5D%20reversed%20the%20impact%20of%20COVID-19%20on%20the%20TB%20programme.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20many%20as%2013%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WHO%20report%2C%20which%20reported%20major%20case%20detection%20reductions%20in%202020%20and%202021%20rebounded%20to%202019%20levels.%20However%2C%20the%20report%20also%20put%20a%20caveat%20to%20this%20achievement%20and%20its%20understanding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20highlighted%20that%20some%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98rebound%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20case%20detection%20numbers%20and%20reported%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98new%20case%E2%80%99%20in%202022%20could%20probably%20be%20%E2%80%98a%20sizeable%20backlog%20of%20people%20who%20developed%20TB%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eprevious%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20years%20%5Bof%202020%20and%202021%5D.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20improved%20case%20detection%20levels%20for%202022%20might%20not%20be%20the%20new%20cases%20found%20in%202022%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eper%20se%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20but%20some%20of%20them%20which%20fell%20through%20the%20cracks%20in%202020%20and%202021.%20The%20backlog%20could%20be%20a%20result%20of%20shutdown%20of%20all%20essential%20services%2C%20including%20TB%20services%2C%20in%20the%20two%20pandemic%20years%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20their%20diagnosis%20got%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edelayed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20far%20as%20year%202022%20was%20concerned%2C%20the%20WHO%20reported%2C%2010%20countries%20continue%20to%20account%20for%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20the%20cases%20missed.%20India%20was%20the%20top%20contributor%20to%20this%20share%20as%20it%20accounted%20for%2018%25%20of%20such%20cases.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20Indonesia%2C%20Philippines%2C%20Nigeria%20and%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20a%20global%20perspective%2C%20efforts%20to%20increase%20levels%20of%20case%20detection%20are%20of%20particular%20importance%20in%20these%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted%2C%20highlighting%20the%20significance%20of%20improved%20diagnostic%20tools.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%20milestones%20missed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20health%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20release%20highlighted%20India%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20reducing%20the%20TB%20incidence.%20%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20efforts%20have%20resulted%20in%20reduction%20of%20TB%20incidence%20by%2016%25%20in%202022%20(from%202015)%20almost%20double%20the%20pace%20at%20which%20global%20TB%20incidence%20is%20declining%20(which%20is%208.7%25)%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20it%20did%20not%20say%20India%2C%20though%20just%20like%20many%20other%20countries%2C%20was%20far%20off%20target%20to%20achieve%20the%20targeted%20goal%20and%20the%20success%20was%20far%20from%20insufficient.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20the%20WHO%2C%202018%2C%20had%20come%20up%20with%20some%20interim%20TB%20targets%20to%20be%20achieved%20so%20as%20to%20eliminate%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20top%20killer%20by%202030.%20The%20interim%20targets%20are%20known%20as%20first%20%E2%80%98End%20TB%20Strategy%E2%80%99%20milestones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20such%20targets%20was%20the%20cumulative%20reduction%20in%20the%20TB%20incidence%20rate%20in%202025%20by%20about%20half%20as%20compared%20to%20the%202015%20levels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20press%20release%20said%20India%20could%20reduce%20the%20TB-related%20deaths%20by%2018%25%20in%202022%20as%20compared%20to%202015%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20almost%20at%20par%20with%20global%20reduction%20levels%20of%2019%25.%20However%2C%20this%20%E2%80%98achievement%E2%80%99%2C%20too%2C%20is%20far%20off%20the%20mark.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20target%20was%20to%20reduce%20TB-related%20deaths%20from%202015%20to%202025%20by%2075%25.%20Going%20by%20the%20current%20pace%2C%20most%20of%20the%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20will%20most%20likely%20miss%20this%20goal%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20challenges%20galore%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDrug-resistant%20TB%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20major%20concern%20for%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResistance%20to%20rifampicin%20%E2%80%93%20the%20most%20effective%20first%20line%20drug%20against%20TB%20%E2%80%93%20is%20of%20greatest%20concern%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WHO.%20The%20form%20of%20TB%20that%20is%20resistant%20to%20rifampicin%20and%20isoniazid%20is%20defined%20as%20multidrug-resistant%20TB%20(MDR-TB).%20Both%20MDR-TB%20and%20rifampicin-resistant%20TB%20(RR-TB)%20require%20treatment%20with%20second-line%20drugs%2C%20which%20is%20not%20only%20very%20expensive%2C%20prolonged%20but%20also%20leads%20to%20various%20other%20direct%20and%20indirect%20consequences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUsually%2C%20a%20patient%20may%20become%20resistant%20to%20the%20first%20line%20of%20drugs%20during%20the%20course%20of%20TB%20treatment%20due%20to%20missing%20drug%20doses%20either%20due%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwill-the-un-high-level-meeting-address-indias-problem-of-tb-drugs-stock-out-situation%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estock-out%20of%20drugs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20improper%20adherence%20to%20the%C2%A0%20medicine%20schedule.%20Some%20of%20the%20newly-diagnosed%20TB%20cases%20could%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ealso%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20be%20that%20of%20DR-TB%2C%20as%20a%20resistant%20form%20of%20infection%20got%20transmitted%20from%20an%20infected%20DR-TB%20patient%20to%20an%20otherwise%20healthy%20person.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20countries%20accounted%20for%2042%25%20of%20the%20estimated%20global%20number%20of%20people%20who%20developed%20MDR%20or%20RR-TB%20in%202022%3A%20India%20(27%25)%2C%20Philippines%20(7.5%25)%20and%20Russia%20(7.5%25).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-tb-patients-across-india-struggle-with-acute-drug-shortages-govt-denies-but-who-worried%5C%22%3EWatch%20%7C%20TB%20Patients%20Across%20India%20Struggle%20With%20Acute%20Drug%20Shortages%2C%20Govt%20Denies%20but%20WHO%20Worried%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20in%202021%20issued%20updated%20guidelines%20for%20diagnostics.%20It%20recommended%20that%20rapid%20molecular%20tests%20should%20replace%20the%20tradition%20sputum%20microscopy%20tests%20as%20the%20former%20have%20high%20diagnostic%20accuracy%20and%20help%20in%20early%20detection%20of%20TB%20or%20to%20understand%20if%20the%20patient%20is%20resistant%20to%20a%20drug.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20the%20current%20TB%20report%20reveals%20that%2C%20in%20India%2C%20less%20than%2020%25%20of%20all%20the%20notified%20cases%20were%20detected%20through%20the%20WHO-recommended%20molecular%20kits%20against%20the%20least%20target%20of%2080%25.%20Globally%2C%2055%20countries%20have%20achieved%20this%20target.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExpenditure%20on%20health%2C%20which%20is%20incurred%20out-of-pocket%20by%20patients%E2%80%99%20households%20on%20their%20own%2C%20is%20a%20major%20deterrent%20in%20fights%20against%20all%20illnesses%2C%20including%20TB.%20If%20more%20than%2010%25%20of%20the%20annual%20household%20income%20is%20spent%20on%20treatment%20of%20any%20kind%20of%20illness%2C%20the%20WHO%20defines%20it%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccatastrophic%20health%20expenditure%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20India%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20more%20than%2020%25%20of%20the%20140%20crore%20population%20in%202022%20had%20to%20incur%20catastrophic%20expenditure%20on%20health%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20TB%2C%20if%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20direct%20medical%20expenditures%2C%20non-medical%20expenditures%20and%20indirect%20costs%20such%20as%20income%20losses%20that%20amount%20to%20more%20than%2020%25%20of%20total%20household%20income%2C%20it%20is%20termed%20%E2%80%98catastrophic%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20Globally%2C%20about%2050%25%20of%20all%20TB%20patients%20had%20to%20face%20this%20dire%20situation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20for%20India%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20TB%20patients%20spending%20catastrophically%20on%20TB%20is%20not%20known%2C%20the%20WHO%20report%20highlighted%20that%20the%20percentage%20of%20TB%20patients%20facing%20such%20a%20situation%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20much%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehigher%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethan%20the%20percentage%20of%20the%20general%20population%20facing%20catastrophic%20expenditures%20on%20healthcare%2C%20for%20all%20the%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20current%20TB%20report%20also%20said%20India%20was%20able%20to%20reach%20the%20treatment%20coverage%20of%2080%25%20of%20all%20the%20estimated%20cases%20in%202022%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20ensuring%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20patients%20availed%20the%20medicine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%2C%20in%20its%20current%20report%20also%20did%20a%20downward%20revision%20of%20TB%20mortality%20figures%20for%20India%20which%20was%20published%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20global%20TB%20report.%20Government%E2%80%99s%20press%20release%20alluded%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnewer%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20shared%20with%20the%20WHO%20after%20the%20publication%20of%20its%20report.%20The%20WHO%20specified%20that%20it%20revised%20the%20figures%20owing%20to%C2%A0%20the%20new%20cause-of-death%20data%20that%20emanated%20from%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20sample%20registration%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20current%20report%2C%203%2C42%2C000%20TB%20patients%20died%20in%202022%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699511973000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09115911%2F4903953427_9db86dcdff_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Ftb-tuberculosis-india-goals-detection%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Global%20Tuberculosis%20Report%2C%202023'%20says%20India%20was%20able%20to%20recover%20losses%20in%20TB%20detection%20in%202022%20that%20it%20had%20made%20in%20the%20two%20pandemic%20years.%20However%2C%20in%20line%20with%20global%20trends%2C%20India%20is%20most%20likely%20to%20fail%20in%20reaching%20key%20goals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Ftb-tuberculosis-india-goals-detection%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Samvat%202080%3A%20Stock%20picks%20by%20HDFC%20Sec%2C%20Kotak%20Sec%2C%20ICICI%20Direct%2C%20JM%20Financial%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699511873000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-11%2F08%2Ffull%2F1667930235-4251.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsamvat-2080-stock-picks-by-hdfc-sec-kotak-sec-icici-direct-jm-financial-123110900361_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Here's%20a%20list%20of%20Diwali%20picks%20recommended%20by%20top%20brokerage%20and%20research%20firms%20that%20can%20help%20you%20build%20your%20portfolio%20for%20Samvat%202080.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsamvat-2080-stock-picks-by-hdfc-sec-kotak-sec-icici-direct-jm-financial-123110900361_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsamvat-2080-stock-picks-by-hdfc-sec-kotak-sec-icici-direct-jm-financial-123110900361_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsamvat-2080-stock-picks-by-hdfc-sec-kotak-sec-icici-direct-jm-financial-123110900361_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hollywood%20actors'%20union%20agrees%20tentative%20deal%20to%20end%20four-month%20strike%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699511841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F41D7%2Fproduction%2F_131655861_5801c7d1027727f359cd6218d48519f8b71f7e820_576_5875_33052000x1125.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%