%2C%20the%20scenes%20in%20the%20scroll%20ended%20with%20him%20vanquishing%20his%20maternal%20uncle%20Kansh%20(Kanxa%20Bodh).%20In%20all%2C%20there%20were%20twenty-seven%20scenes%2C%20woven%20on%20the%20loom%2C%20picked%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3EBhagavad%20Purana%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20holy%20book%20that%20is%20typically%20placed%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3Emonikut%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20altar%2C%20at%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekirtan-ghar%3C%2Fem%3E%2F%3Cem%3Enaam-ghar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Vaishnava%20prayer%20hall.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20other%20important%20design%20features%20from%20that%20sacred%20textile%20were%20the%20use%20of%20verses%20in%20classical%20Assamese%20to%20describe%20the%20scenes%20from%20%3Cem%3EKalio%20Damana%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20play%20penned%20by%20Sankardev%20to%20narrate%20the%20tale%20of%20little%20Krishna%20crushing%20the%20serpent-demon%20Kaliya%2C%20and%20the%20depiction%20of%20Vishnu%E2%80%99s%20incarnations.%20In%20keeping%20with%20the%20tale%20from%20Krishna%E2%80%99s%20birthplace%20Brindaban%20(Vrindavan)%2C%20the%20name%20of%20the%20cloth%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EBastra%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20called%20Brindabani.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20353px)%2085vw%2C%20353px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09113345%2F81PBJENm12L._SL1500_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22353%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09113345%2F81PBJENm12L._SL1500_.jpg%20822w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09113345%2F81PBJENm12L._SL1500_-206x300.jpg%20206w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09113345%2F81PBJENm12L._SL1500_-701x1024.jpg%20701w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684227%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22515%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESangeeta%20Barooah%20Pisharoty%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Assamese%3A%20A%20Portrait%20of%20a%20Community%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EAleph%20Books%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESankardev%2C%20who%20resided%20in%20Patbausi%20then%2C%20set%20up%20a%20monastery%20where%20he%20visualised%20the%20scenes%20for%20the%20weavers%20and%20how%20they%20could%20be%20illustrated%20on%20textile.%20Twelve%20strips%20of%20woven%20textile%20of%20equal%20size%20were%20born%20of%20that%20effort.%20The%20story%20goes%20that%20Sankardev%20had%20to%20seek%20the%20help%20of%20three%20dozen%20people%20to%20cart%20the%20bundles%20to%20Patbausi%20Satra%20from%20the%20karkhana%2C%20the%20weaving%20shed.%20Thereafter%2C%20the%20bunch%20was%20loaded%20on%20to%20a%20boat%20to%20reach%20the%20royal%20palace%20at%20Koch%20Behar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGeneral%20Silarai%20and%20King%20Naranarayan%20were%20over%20the%20moon%20to%20see%20the%20Lord%E2%80%99s%20story%20recounted%20in%20delicate%20weave.%20They%20offered%20to%20hand%20over%20to%20Sankardev%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20Barpeta%20principality%20as%20a%20present%20which%20he%20declined%2C%20though%20his%20grandson%20Ram%20Rai%20later%20took%20charge%20of%20it.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20belief%20among%20a%20wide%20section%20of%20people%20in%20Assam%20has%20been%20that%20after%20the%20scrolls%20were%20formally%20presented%20to%20the%20king%2C%20they%20were%20preserved%20at%20Madhupur%20Satra%20in%20Koch%20Behar%2C%20the%20last%20abode%20of%20Sankardev%20(the%20Satra%20is%20in%20present-day%20West%20Bengal).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scroll%20seems%20to%20have%20vanished%20from%20the%20monastery%20one%20fine%20day%20though.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20ensued%20is%20an%20interesting%20story%20of%20trade%2C%20preservation%2C%20loot%20and%20discovery%20spanning%20several%20centuries%20and%20three%20countries%20before%20parts%20of%20the%20scroll%20could%20be%20traced%2C%20all%20thanks%20to%20a%20British%20journalist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBack%20in%201904%2C%20Perceval%20Landon%2C%20a%20journalist%20associated%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20donated%20to%20the%20British%20Museum%20in%20London%20about%20nine-and-a-half%20inches%20of%20a%20splendidly%20woven%20work%20with%20silk%20borders.%20Landon%20had%20accompanied%20the%20British%20expedition%20to%20Tibet%20under%20Sir%20Francis%20Younghusband%20in%201903-1904%20to%20establish%20trade%20with%20Lhasa%2C%20and%20had%20brought%20that%20tapestry%20home.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Assamese%20community%20had%20long%20concluded%20that%20the%20Brindabani%20Bastra%20was%20a%20lost%20artefact.%20And%20for%20about%20eighty-five%20years%2C%20the%20piece%20donated%20by%20Landon%20remained%20identified%20in%20the%20Museum%E2%80%99s%20catalogue%20as%20%E2%80%98Tibetan%20Silk%20Lampas%E2%80%99%20simply%20because%20he%20had%20sourced%20it%20from%20that%20region.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201992%2C%20a%20British%20art%20scholar%2C%20Rosemary%20Crill%2C%20then%20associated%20with%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20in%20London%20as%20a%20senior%20curator%2C%20which%20also%20possesses%20a%20similar%20piece%20with%20%3Cem%3Elampa%3C%2Fem%3E%20weave%2C%20identified%20it%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20some%20other%20similar%20pieces%20preserved%20at%20the%20British%20Museum%20and%20elsewhere%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20as%20belonging%20to%20the%20legacy%20of%20the%20most%20precious%20Assamese%20weaving%20tradition%2C%20the%20Brindabani%20Bastra.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20year%2C%20Crill%20put%20together%20a%20well-received%20exhibition%20titled%20%E2%80%98Fabric%20of%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20which%20she%20also%20included%20the%20piece%20of%20Brindabani%20Bastra%20from%20the%20museum%E2%80%99s%20collection%2C%20raising%20eyebrows%20in%20faraway%20Assam.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20T.%20Richard%20Burton%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20South%20Asian%20department%20at%20the%20British%20Museum%2C%20the%20panel%20of%20Brindabani%20Bastra%20%E2%80%93%20presently%20preserved%20as%20a%20wall%20hanging%20at%20the%20Museum%20%E2%80%93%20was%20traced%20to%20the%20Gobshi%20Temple%20near%20Gyantse%20in%20Tibet.%20It%20probably%20ended%20up%20there%20through%20a%20trading%20route%20between%20medieval%20Assam%20and%20the%20neighbouring%20country%2C%20or%20through%20Bhutan%2C%20with%20which%20the%20Koch%20country%20had%20shared%20its%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20curators%20like%20Burton%20have%20supposed%20that%20the%20pieces%20might%20have%20reached%20the%20Tibetan%20monastery%20separately%2C%20not%20as%20woven%20originally%2C%20they%20were%20stitched%20there%2C%20by%20adding%20broad%20silk%20borders%20in%20the%20style%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Etankha%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20put%20up%20in%20the%20monastery.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20present%20display%20at%20the%20museum%20has%20those%20silk%20borders.%20Burton%20had%20reasoned%20that%20the%20pieces%20could%20be%20immaculately%20preserved%20at%20the%20monastery%20for%20centuries%20perhaps%20because%20smoke%20from%20butter%20lamps%20and%20incense%20protected%20it%20from%20moths.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20lampa%20weave%20used%20by%20the%20Assamese%20weavers%20on%20those%20pieces%20meant%20they%20used%20two%20warp%20systems%20with%20two%20or%20more%20wefts%20to%20produce%20the%20highly%20lavish%20texture%20of%20the%20textiles.%20Burton%2C%20who%20visited%20Majuli%20in%202016%20chasing%20the%20story%20behind%20the%20textile%20preserved%20at%20the%20British%20Museum%20and%20went%20back%20to%20London%20to%20curate%20an%20exhibition%20titled%20%E2%80%98Krishna%20in%20the%20Garden%20of%20Assam%E2%80%99%2C%20documented%20in%20a%20short%20video%20that%20the%20technique%20is%20still%20being%20used%20by%20Assamese%20weavers%20even%20in%20cotton%20textiles%2C%20say%2C%20in%20weaving%20a%20%3Cem%3Egamusa%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20the%20method%20is%20commonly%20termed%20in%20Assamese%20as%20%3Cem%3Ebhul%20bosa%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBurton%E2%80%99s%20Assam%20visit%20was%20significant%20as%20he%20could%20successfully%20link%20the%20motifs%20and%20writings%20on%20the%20museum%20pieces%20and%20the%20lived%20traditions%20in%20Majuli%20and%20the%20prevalent%20Sankari%20culture%20in%20the%20northeastern%20state.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20clay%20masks%20made%20in%20Majuli%2C%20till%20date%2C%20of%20various%20characters%20to%20dramatise%20the%20%3Cem%3EAnkiya%20Nat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(plays)%20of%20Sankardev%2C%20are%20readied%20as%20per%20the%20description%20of%20the%20saint%20in%20his%20writings%2C%20and%20their%20look%20matches%20those%20of%20the%20motifs%20woven%20in%20the%20museum%20pieces%20and%20the%20text%20knitted%20into%20the%20pieces%20in%20classical%20Assamese.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20visit%20to%20Majuli%20had%20helped%20Burton%20contextualise%20the%20cloth%20at%20the%20British%20Museum%20with%20a%20lived%20culture%20and%20help%20revive%20for%20posterity%20a%20significant%20chapter%20of%20Assamese%20weaving%20traditions%20that%20was%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20lost.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20540px)%2085vw%2C%20540px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09101135%2F689ad8b8-dea2-4080-b5b6-dbee9e903983.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09101135%2F689ad8b8-dea2-4080-b5b6-dbee9e903983.jpg%20540w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09101135%2F689ad8b8-dea2-4080-b5b6-dbee9e903983-135x300.jpg%20135w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09101135%2F689ad8b8-dea2-4080-b5b6-dbee9e903983-461x1024.jpg%20461w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684207%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20centuries%20old%20Vaishnava%20Satra%20in%20Majuli%20set%20up%20on%20the%20ideals%20of%20saint%20Sankardev%20photo%20Sangeeta%20Barooah%20Pisharoty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20Burton%20has%20stated%20that%20the%20British%20Museum%20piece%20dates%20back%20to%20around%201680.%20If%20the%20dating%20is%20correct%2C%20that%20piece%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20the%20original%20one%20woven%20during%20Sankardev%E2%80%99s%20lifetime%3B%20he%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20passed%20away%20in%201568.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20then%20also%20comes%20across%20is%20that%20following%20the%20path%20laid%20by%20the%20great%20saint%2C%20there%20may%20have%20been%20successive%20endeavours%20to%20weave%20such%20sacred%20textiles%20in%20Vaishnava%20tradition%2C%20and%20a%20new%20school%20of%20devotional%20textile%20art%20using%20the%20lampa%20weave%20must%20have%20been%20prevalent%20in%20medieval%20Assam%2C%20something%20akin%20to%20the%20tankha%20art%20in%20Buddhist%20monasteries.%20Quite%20a%20few%20similarities%20can%20be%20drawn%20between%20Buddhism%20and%20the%20Neo-Vaishnavism%20of%20Sankardev%20anyway.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20there%20could%20have%20been%20such%20a%20prevalent%20practice%20even%20after%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20saint%20perhaps%20justifies%20the%20reason%20why%20there%20are%20several%20such%20pieces%20of%20Brindabani%20Bastra%2C%20which%20the%20Western%20scholars%20date%20to%20the%20seventeenth%20century.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20point%20to%20note%20is%2C%20as%20per%20Crill%2C%20not%20all%20of%20them%20match%20in%20texture%20with%20each%20other.%20Such%20pieces%20are%20well-preserved%20in%20the%20Guimet%20Museum%20in%20Paris%2C%20the%20Chepstow%20Museum%20in%20Wales%2C%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20in%20London%2C%20and%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20County%20Museum%20of%20Art%20and%20the%20Philadelphia%20Museum%20of%20Art%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20noted%20Sankari%20studies%20scholar%20Sanjiv%20Borkakoty%2C%20there%20is%20a%20high%20possibility%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20school%20of%20sacred%20weave%20that%20Sankardev%E2%80%99s%20venture%20had%20given%20birth%20to%20in%20Kamrup.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20my%20mind%2C%20the%20British%20scholars%20are%20correct%3B%20the%20pieces%20available%20at%20the%20London%20Museum%20or%20at%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20are%20not%20the%20original%20ones%3B%20they%20were%20the%20later%20products%20that%20weavers%20trained%20by%20Sankardev%20had%20woven.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20to%20how%20such%20sacred%20weaves%20might%20have%20reached%20Tibet%2C%20Borkakoty%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20nothing%20to%20be%20surprised%20at%3B%20Assam%20and%20Tibet%20had%20trade%20relations%20for%20long%20and%20one%20of%20the%20items%20for%20commerce%20was%20textile.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignificantly%2C%20in%20the%20catalogue%20for%20the%201992%20exhibition%20titled%20%E2%80%98Vrindavani%20Vastra%20%E2%80%94%20Figured%20Silks%20from%20Assam%E2%80%99%2C%20Crill%20had%20written%20on%20the%20Assamese%20tapestry%2C%20that%20those%20scrolls%20depicting%20scenes%20from%20Krishna%E2%80%99s%20childhood%20tracing%20back%20to%20Assam%20might%20have%20been%20the%20precursor%20to%20what%20the%20Assamese%20community%20presently%20calls%20the%20%3Cem%3Eguxain%20kapur%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20the%20cloth%20with%20religious%20and%20floral%20motifs%20with%20the%20words%20of%20the%20Lord%20in%20the%20Assamese%20script%20to%20be%20used%20at%20the%20altar%20or%20%3Cem%3Ethapona%3C%2Fem%3E%20cover%20of%20a%20Vaishnava%20monastery.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20thus%20likely%20that%20those%20in%20use%20today%20or%20in%20the%20recent%20past%20represent%20the%20much%20simplified%20tail-end%20of%20the%20design%20tradition%2C%20in%20which%20the%20complex%20registers%20of%20small%2C%20finely-drawn%20figures%20have%20been%20abandoned%20in%20favour%20of%20fewer%2C%20large-scale%20motifs.%20The%20design%20elements%20may%20also%20have%20lost%20their%20original%20identity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202017%2C%20yet%20another%20significant%20event%20took%20place%20around%20the%20Brindabani%20Bastra%20in%20the%20UK.%20The%20event%20was%20at%20the%20Chepstow%20Museum%20in%20Wales.%20Titled%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHidden%20in%20the%20Lining%20%E2%80%94%20Krishna%20in%20the%20Garden%20of%20Assam%3A%20Inside%20an%20Eighteenth-Century%20Banyan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20was%20a%20study%20highlighting%20an%20important%20connection%20that%20the%20nine-metre-long%20piece%20at%20the%20British%20Museum%20had%20with%20the%20lining%20of%20a%20luxurious%20gown%20preserved%20at%20the%20Chepstow%20Museum.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20gown%20was%20a%20Banyan%2C%20a%20European%20unisex%20morning%20or%20night%20robe%20from%20the%20seventeenth-eighteenth%20century%2C%20said%20to%20be%20inspired%20by%20the%20Japanese%20kimono.%20Banyan%20was%20part%20of%20elite%20fashion%20which%20had%20seeped%20into%20high-society%20colonial%20India%20too%20as%20a%20house%20gown%20worn%20by%20men%20and%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBurton%20and%20Crill%20were%20among%20the%20speakers%20at%20the%202017%20event.%20By%20then%2C%20the%20exhibition%20curated%20by%20Burton%20at%20the%20British%20Museum%20had%20placed%20the%20eighteenth-century%20Banyan%20coat%20from%20the%20Chepstow%20Museum%20alongside%20the%20Brindabani%20Bastra%20wall%20hanging%20to%20underline%20that%20the%20lining%20of%20that%20coat%20might%20have%20been%20cut%20from%20the%20same%20piece%20as%20that%20of%20the%20wall%20hanging.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20coat%E2%80%99s%20lining%20also%20has%20the%20classical%20Assamese%20texts%20typically%20used%20in%20the%20Bastra.%20It%20is%20most%20likely%20that%20the%20lining%20was%20much%20older%20than%20the%20garment%20stitched%20in%20the%20eighteenth%20century%2C%20the%20experts%20suggested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20museum%20curator%20Anne%20Rainsbury%20mentioned%20that%20the%20piece%20had%20reached%20them%20from%20the%20Cobb%20family%20who%20had%20owned%20the%20Caldicot%20Castle.%20Joseph%20Cobb%E2%80%99s%20wife%20had%20links%20to%20the%20East%20India%20Company.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20this%20is%20where%20the%20Assamese%20lining%20was%20sourced%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20underlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESusan%20North%2C%20senior%20curator%20of%20fashion%20at%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%2C%20highlighting%20the%20eastern%20roots%20of%20the%20Banyan%20at%20that%20event%2C%20emphasised%20on%20that%20kind%20of%20garment%20representing%20%E2%80%98exoticism%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cmark%3E%3C%2Fmark%3E%3Cspan%3EVisual%20records%20specialist%20at%20the%20UK%20National%20Archives%2C%20Olivia%20Gecseg%2C%20also%20rightly%20pointed%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CSusan%E2%80%99s%20explanation%20points%20us%20to%20the%20answer%20of%20the%20broader%20question%20of%20why%20a%20sacred%20textile%20is%20lining%20a%20banyan%3B%20that%20is%2C%20that%20the%20owner%20had%20no%20idea%20of%20the%20cloth%E2%80%99s%20meaning.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20the%20banyan%E2%80%99s%20production%2C%20probably%20sent%20to%20a%20tailor%20to%20be%20made%20up%2C%20the%20cloth%20had%20been%20detached%20from%20its%20cultural%20roots%2C%20thereby%20left%20open%20for%20appropriation%20into%20Western%20fashion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20point%20of%20curiosity%20among%20that%20group%20of%20Western%20curators%20was%3A%20what%20was%20a%20scroll%20considered%20sacred%20in%20the%20Hindu%20context%20doing%20at%20a%20Buddhist%20monastery%20in%20Tibet%3F%20To%20my%20mind%2C%20the%20answer%20may%20perhaps%20be%20found%20if%20it%20is%20placed%20vis-a-vis%20the%20centuries-old%20practice%20of%20Bhutanese%20Buddhist%20monks%20visiting%20the%20Haigrib%20Madhab%20temple%20in%20Lower%20Assam.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Hindus%20of%20Assam%20worship%20the%20idol%20at%20the%20temple%20rebuilt%20by%20Koch%20king%20Naranarayan%20as%20a%20reincarnation%20of%20Vishnu%2C%20the%20Buddhist%20monks%20continue%20to%20pray%20there%2C%20considering%20it%20the%20burial%20ground%20of%20the%20Buddha%2C%20which%20some%20also%20believe%20to%20be%20that%20of%20the%20revered%20Buddhist%20monk%20Padmasambhava.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20a%20belief%20exists%20in%20Tibet%20too%2C%20as%20highlighted%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20book.%20Vishnu%2C%20whose%20incarnation%20Krishna%20was%20depicted%20in%20the%20Assamese%20scrolls%2C%20was%20not%20so%20much%20outside%20of%20their%20devotional%20pale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEver%20since%20the%20news%20spread%20in%20Assam%20about%20Crill%E2%80%99s%20discovery%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20steady%20demand%20from%20within%20the%20community%20on%20subsequent%20state%20governments%20to%20pressurise%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20employ%20diplomatic%20channels%20to%20bring%20the%20prized%20artefact%20home.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20mid-2020%2C%20Kanaksen%20Deka%2C%20well-known%20Assamese%20editor-commentator%20and%20a%20strong%20voice%20behind%20that%20popular%20demand%2C%20had%20told%20me%20about%20penning%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20during%20his%20first%20term%20with%20a%20suggestion%20that%20it%20be%20displayed%20at%20the%20podium%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20where%20prized%20artefacts%20from%20several%20186%20member%20countries%20are%20exhibited%20to%20represent%20their%20culture.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20none%20from%20India%20at%20the%20moment.%20Can%20his%20government%20not%20use%20diplomatic%20channels%20to%20display%20some%20bit%20of%20what%20I%20saw%20at%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20in%20London%20at%20the%20UN%20podium%20as%20a%20proud%20insignia%20of%20India%3F%20Unfortunately%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20get%20any%20response%20from%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20Deka%20told%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699505941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09094622%2FUntitled-design-9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-excerpt-sangeeta-barooah-pisharoty-tapestry-assam%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20makes%20a%20textile%20'lost'%3F%20How%20do%20we%20get%20it%20back%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-excerpt-sangeeta-barooah-pisharoty-tapestry-assam%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kamala%20Harris%20celebrates%20early%20Diwali%20at%20her%20residence%3B%20says%20the%20world%20is%20facing%20a%20'difficult%20and%20dark%20moment'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699505208000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105084973%2Cimgsize-656492.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fkamala-harris-celebrates-early-diwali-at-her-residence-says-the-world-is-facing-a-difficult-and-dark-moment%2Farticleshow%2F105084905.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105084905.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20celebrated%20Diwali%20at%20her%20official%20residence%20and%20addressed%20the%20guests%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20importance%20of%20celebrating%20the%20festival%20of%20light%20during%20difficul