its%20own%20to%20take%20out%20New%20York's%20rats%20for%20good.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City%20has%20deployed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-new-rat-killing-method-highly-successful-expanding-new-areas-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20method%20for%20killing%20rats%3C%2Fa%3E%20that's%20so%20effective%20nearly%20every%20rat%20targeted%20with%20it%20has%20been%20eliminated%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20city's%20notorious%20rat%20problem%20is%20solved%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20method%20involves%20pumping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-exterminator-dead-rat-bodies-carbon-monoxide-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarbon%20monoxide%20into%20rat%20burrows%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ultimately%20suffocating%20the%20rodents%20inside.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20quick%2C%26quot%3B%20exterminator%20Matt%20Deodato%2C%20owner%20of%20Urban%20Pest%20Management%20previously%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20carbon%20monoxide%20method%20successfully%20eliminated%20100%20burrows%20on%20a%20stretch%20of%20East%2086th%20Street%20on%20the%20Upper%20East%20Side%2C%20and%20there%20are%20already%20plans%20to%20try%20it%20in%20new%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20will%20likely%20take%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20that%20to%20take%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarbon-monoxide-nyc-rat-exterminator-clap-cheer-free-beer-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20City's%20rats%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Munshi-South%2C%20a%20biologist%20at%20Fordham%20University%20who%20studies%20urban%20rats%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20while%20the%20carbon%20monoxide%20method%20will%20kill%20the%20rats%20in%20the%20burrows%20that%20are%20targeted%2C%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Blimited%20strategy%26quot%3B%20that%20will%20result%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Blimited%20victory.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20haven't%20solved%20the%20underlying%20issues%20of%20access%20to%20food%20and%20garbage%20and%20harborage%20for%20the%20rats%20to%20nest%20in%2C%20then%20they%20will%20come%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-hiring-bloodthirsty-director-rodent-mitigation-fight-rats-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekill%20rats%20inhabiting%20burrows%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20park%20or%20near%20a%20building%2C%20eventually%20other%20rats%20from%20nearby%20will%20move%20in%2C%20or%20if%20there%20are%20any%20survivors%20they%20might%20reproduce%20and%20repopulate%20a%20burrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunshi-South%20said%20similar%20methods%20have%20been%20used%20in%20the%20past%2C%20including%20with%20dry%20ice%20in%20parks%20in%20lower%20Manhattan%20that%20had%20hundreds%20of%20rat%20burrows.%20Through%20daily%20and%20intensive%20use%20of%20dry%20ice%20and%20monitoring%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20burrows%20to%20only%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you%20stop%20doing%20that%20for%20a%20period%20of%20time%20and%20come%20back%20next%20year%2C%20the%20rats%20are%20thriving%20again%2C%20%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that's%20why%20it's%20a%20limited%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeodato%20agreed%20that%20the%20method%20is%20not%20a%20permanent%20solution%2C%20adding%20that%20you%20also%20need%20to%20eliminate%20their%20food%20supply%20and%20a%20place%20for%20them%20to%20nest%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20any%20rats%20from%20coming%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20carbon%20monoxide%20method%20can%20also%20only%20be%20used%20in%20a%20well-ventilated%2C%20outdoor%20area%20to%20avoid%20poisoning%20the%20person%20applying%20it%20or%20other%20people%2C%20Munshi-South%20said.%20So%20it%20can't%20be%20used%20on%20rats%20that%20live%20in%20subway%20stations%2C%20sewers%2C%20or%20even%20too