20He%20also%20spoke%20about%20the%20reasons%20for%20targeting%20limbs%2C%20especially%20those%20of%20the%20injured%2C%20the%20immediate%20and%20long-term%20impacts%20on%20hospitals%2C%20the%20mental%20trauma%20of%20healthcare%20workers%20who%20are%20working%20non-stop%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20response%20from%20the%20medical%20community%20against%20the%20conflict%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20text%20of%20the%20interview%20is%20reproduced%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBanjot%20Kaur%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20You%20take%20a%20very%20strong%20stand%20and%20say%20that%20the%20recent%20attacks%20on%20healthcare%20facilities%20in%20Gaza%20are%20the%20most%20%E2%80%9Cegregious%E2%80%9D%20in%20our%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20history%E2%80%9D.%20In%20an%20entire%20paragraph%2C%20you%20have%20referred%20to%20how%20the%20%E2%80%9Cde-development%E2%80%9D%20of%20Palestinian%20healthcare%20facilities%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9CIsraeli%20occupation%E2%80%9D%20preceded%20these%20attacks.%20Why%20do%20you%20call%20these%20the%20most%20egregious%20and%20horrific%20of%20all%20the%20attacks%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EJames%20Smith%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThank%20you%20Banjot%2C%20and%20thank%20you%20for%20the%20opportunity%20to%20speak%20to%20you%20about%20an%20issue%20that%20as%20we%20all%20know%20is%20timely%20and%20also%20horrific%20in%20its%20scale%20and%20severity%20of%20violence.%20I%20think%20we%20all%20need%20to%20be%20talking%20about%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20the%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20military%20wing%20of%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%20at%20the%20present%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20we%20described%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20at%20the%20moment%20as%20the%20most%20egregious%20in%20a%20long%20history%20is%20for%20precisely%20the%20scale%20of%20violence%20%5Bwhich%5D%20far%20surpasses%20anything%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20Israeli%20violence%20directed%20towards%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20statistics%20from%20the%20UN%20Office%20for%20the%20High%20Commissioner%20of%20Humanitarian%20Affairs%20tell%20us%20that%20as%20of%20yesterday%20evening%20%5BNovember%205%5D%2C%20almost%2010%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20since%20October%207.%20The%20number%20currently%20stands%20at%209%2C488%2C%20with%20hundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20still%20trapped%20under%20the%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20we%20really%20wanted%20to%20articulate%20in%20this%20paper%20%5Beditorial%5D%20is%20that%20this%20violence%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20appeared%20out%20of%20nowhere.%20This%20is%20the%20latest%20iteration%20in%20a%20long%20history%20of%20violence%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20important%20for%20us%20as%20healthcare%20workers%20and%20peace%20advocates%2C%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20as%20humanitarian%20workers%20to%20understand%20the%20context%20in%20which%20violence%20is%20committed%2C%20who%20%5Bis%5D%20committing%20%5Bthe%5D%20violence%20against%20whom%2C%20under%20what%20political%20economic%20and%20social%20circumstances%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%E2%80%99ve%20tried%20to%20articulate%20in%20part%20in%20this%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FU0L95-6hilU%3Fsi%3DwU3mpo5xnLAndUw3%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20you%20choose%20to%20provide%20a%20political%20context%20in%20your%20paper%3F%20Usually%2C%20healthcare%20workers%20don%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20politics.%20However%2C%20this%20conflict%20is%20all%20about%20politics.%20And%20you%20take%20the%20conflict%20back%20more%20than%2070%20years%2C%20when%20it%20had%20started.%20Why%20did%20you%20choose%20to%20provide%20a%20political%20context%20to%20an%20editorial%20which%20essentially%20appeared%20in%20a%20medical%20journal%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20is%20a%20common%20misconception%20with%20respect%20to%20healthcare%20workers%20and%20medical%20workers.%20Health%20as%20we%20know%20is%20political.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20increasingly%20talk%20about%20the%20political%20determinants%20of%20health%2C%20which%20is%20very%20much%20in%20keeping%20with%20a%20public%20health%20sort%20of%20philosophy%20when%20we%20think%20about%20understanding%20the%20root%20causes%20of%20ill%20health.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20our%20best%20%5Bnot%20only%5D%20for%20our%20patients%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20communities%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20the%20underlying%20causes%20of%20illnesses.%20So%2C%20we%20have%20to%20understand%20the%20political%20dynamics.%20There%20are%20folks%20within%20the%20medical%20profession%20who%20would%20prefer%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20politics%20but%20that%20would%20really%E2%80%A6I%20would%20strongly%20argue%20that%20it%20is%20a%20mistake.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20think%20again%20we%E2%80%99ve%20tried%20in%20some%20small%20way%20to%20speak%2C%20as%20you%E2%80%99ve%20mentioned%2C%20%5Babout%5D%20almost%20a%20100-year%20history.%20Now%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20difficult%20%5Bto%20write%20the%20full%20history%5D%20in%20a%201500-word%20editorial.%20%5BSo%5D%20we%E2%80%99ve%20alluded%20to%20some%20major%20incidents%20or%20moments%20in%20the%20history%20of%20Palestine%20prior%20to%20and%20following%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20in%201948%2C%20but%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%2C%20of%20course%2C%20do%20justice%20to%20that%20full%20history.%20We%E2%80%99re%20trying%20to%20really%20encourage%20folks%20to%20think%20about%20these%20issues%20and%20to%20understand%20that%20drawn-out%20chronology.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20one%20paragraph%2C%20you%20mentioned%20that%20Gazan%20civilians%E2%80%99%20limbs%20have%20been%20specifically%20targeted.%20How%20important%20is%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20mentioned%20this%20because%2C%20again%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20really%20egregious%20example%20of%20violence%20committed%20by%20the%20Israeli%20military%20against%20Palestinian%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20well-documented%20form%20of%20violence.%20In%20fact%2C%20Israeli%20soldiers%20have%20admitted%20to%20this%20as%20a%20military%20tactic.%20It%20was%20mentioned%2C%20as%20I%20say%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20particularly%20horrific%20form%20of%20violence%20and%20what%20we%20see%20here%20is%20almost%20double%20in%20terms%20of%20sort%20of%20military%20strategy%2C%20if%20I%20could%20even%20afford%20%5Bto%20use%5D%20such%20a%20phrase.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20one%20%5Baspect%5D%20to%20inflict%20harm%20on%20the%20individual%2C%20but%20to%20burden%20the%20health%20system%20and%20to%20burden%20social%20services%20as%20they%20are%20to%20be%20provided%20for%20those%20individuals%20who%20are%20now%20left%20with%20various%20forms%20of%20physical%20disability%20%5Bis%20worthy%20of%20attention%2Fworry%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%C2%A0%20curious%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20if%20limbs%20are%20targeted%2C%20is%20it%20more%20effective%20in%20terms%20of%20military%20strategy%3F%20So%2C%20why%20are%20limbs%20so%20particular%20in%20your%20observation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20should%20say%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20a%20military%20strategist%20nor%20would%20I%20want%20to%20be%20but%20what%20I%20would%20postulate%20as%20a%20healthcare%20professional%20is%20that%20you%20have%20a%20situation%20in%20which%20physical%20violence%20is%20being%20committed%20against%20an%20individual.%20So%20they%20are%20left%20with%20a%20life-altering%20injury.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20%5Bthe%20injured%5D%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20killed%2C%20need%20access%20to%20the%20healthcare%20system.%20In%20some%20instances%2C%20they%20will%20become%20dependent%20on%20different%20forms%20of%20social%20support%2C%20either%20family%20or%20other%20social%20networks%2C%20or%20the%20social%20service%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20it%20becomes%20a%20secondary%20burden%20on%20a%20healthcare%20system%20that%20has%20already%20been%20sort%20of%20worn%20away%20by%20the%20Israeli%20blockades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20in%20a%20way%2C%20if%20my%20conclusion%20is%20correct%2C%20this%20is%20to%20inflict%20a%20long-term%20horror%20instead%20of%20just%20killing%20the%20person%20in%20an%20instant.%20Is%20that%20the%20correct%20interpretation%20of%20mine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20be%20my%20interpretation%20as%20well.%20Absolutely.%20So%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20immediate%20violence%2C%20immediate%20physical%20injury%20and%20then%20long-term%20demand%20on%20the%20health%20and%20social%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20reports%20and%2C%20again%2C%20there%20are%20unconfirmed%20reports%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20perhaps%20possible%20to%20confirm%20them%2C%20of%20phosphorus%20being%20used.%20You%20have%20also%20referred%20to%20that%20in%20your%20editorial.%20Can%20you%20recollect%20in%20recent%20history%20if%20phosphorus%20was%20used%20in%20any%20such%20attack%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99m%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorus%20in%20other%20conflicts%20in%20recent%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%20and%20Amnesty%20International%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20reputable%20international%20human%20rights%20organisations%2C%20have%20verified%20the%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorus%20by%20the%20Israeli%20military%20in%20both%20Gaza%20and%20in%20southern%20Lebanon%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20weeks.%20So%2C%20the%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorus%20has%20been%20verified.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20also%20receiving%20reports%20from%20healthcare%20workers%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Gaza%2C%20describing%20burn%20injuries%20consistent%20with%20those%20caused%20by%20white%20phosphorus.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99m%20sure%20many%20readers%20and%20viewers%20will%20know%20%5Bthat%5D%20white%20phosphorus%20in%20contact%20with%20human%20skin%20can%20also%20damage%20the%20respiratory%20system.%20It%20can%20leave%20a%20person%20with%20particularly%20horrific%20injuries%20as%20the%20chemical%20itself%20continues%20to%20burn%20until%20it%20is%20physically%20removed%20from%20the%20skin.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20particularly%20horrific%20form%20of%20incendiary%20weaponry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20you%20mean%20to%20say%20till%20the%20time%20this%20chemical%20remains%20on%20the%20skin%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20burn%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20ignites.%20So%20you%20then%20need%20to%20remove%20it%20in%20its%20entirety%20from%20the%20skin.%20If%20it%20ignites%2C%20it%20will%20just%20continue%20to%20burn.%20So%20%5Bit%5D%20can%20cause%20really%20horrific%20damage%20to%20the%20skin%20and%20to%20soft%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20Gaza%2C%20of%20course%2C%20we%20know%20that%20the%20healthcare%20systems%20are%20particularly%20overwhelmed.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20situation%20was%20different%2C%20say%2C%20where%20healthcare%20systems%20were%20functioning%20normally%2C%20how%20difficult%20would%20it%20have%20been%20to%20treat%20people%20who%20have%20been%20inflicted%20with%20white%20phosphorus-related%20injuries%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20would%20say%20incredibly%20difficult.%20I%20must%20say%20I%E2%80%99m%20fortunate%20enough%20to%20have%20never%20had%20to%20treat%20an%20individual%20with%20a%20white%20phosphorus%20injury.%C2%A0%20I%E2%80%99ve%20never%20worked%20in%20a%20context%20where%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organization%20provides%20a%20lot%20of%20factual%20information%20related%20to%20the%20white%20phosphorus%20chemical%20and%2C%20as%20I%20say%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20this%20kind%20of%20incendiary%20function%20%5Bof%20phosphorus%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20once%20white%20phosphorus%20has%20ignited%2C%20it%20can%20be%20very%20very%20difficult%20to%20extinguish%20this%20sort%20of%20burning%20chemical.%20So%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20severe%20burns%20to%20the%20skin%2C%20even%20penetrating%20as%20deep%20as%20to%20the%20bone%20even%20after%20you%E2%80%99ve%20initially%20treated.%20It%20can%20reignite.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20also%20cause%20damage%20to%20the%20eyes%20and%20to%20the%20respiratory%20tract.%20It%C2%A0%20often%20requires%20debridement%2C%20that%20is%2C%20removal%20of%20damaged%20skin%20or%20soft%20tissue%20and%20in%20the%20case%20of%20extensive%20injuries%2C%20that%20can%2C%20of%20course%2C%20be%20a%20very%20involved%20surgical%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20does%20it%20require%20healthcare%20workers%20from%20across%20specialties%20to%20treat%20a%20person%20with%20a%20phosphorus-related%20injury%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbsolutely%2C%20absolutely!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680092%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20building%20in%20Gaza%20after%20Israel%20launched%20airstrikes%20following%20Hamas%20surprise%20attack.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40UNRWA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20wrote%20that%20after%20the%20US%20attacked%20a%20hospital%20in%20Afghanistan%20in%202015%2C%20the%20UN%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.un.org%2Fen%2F2016%2Fsc12347.doc.htm%5C%22%3Epassed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20resolution%20saying%20that%20no%20healthcare%20facilities%20would%20be%20attacked%20in%20any%20conflict.%20How%20do%20you%20think%20that%20we%20reached%20the%20point%20where%20we%20sort%20of%20undid%20all%20our%20past%20resolutions%20and%20now%20we%20have%20hospitals%20being%20bombed%20and%20ambulances%20being%20hit%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20really%20appreciate%20this%20question%20because%20we%20really%20need%20to%20all%20be%20reflecting%20in%20a%20very%20concerted%20way%20on%20what%20this%20means%20about%20it%20with%20respect%20to%20our%20kind%20of%20collective%20humanity%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20would%20say%2C%20before%20I%20speak%20to%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%20specifically%2C%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20trend%20in%20attacks%20against%20healthcare%20globally.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20attacks%20on%20healthcare%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20attacks%20on%20healthcare%20in%20Sudan.%20This%20is%20not%20an%20isolated%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20mentioned%2C%20the%20UN%20resolution%20of%202016%20was%20a%20commitment%20at%20the%20level%20of%20the%20UN.%20It%20was%20a%20declaration%2C%20it%20was%20a%20commitment%2C%20but%20in%20many%20respects%2C%20as%20we%20know%20of%20many%20UN%20resolutions%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20to%20uphold%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAttacks%20against%20healthcare%20facilities%2C%20ambulances%2C%20and%20healthcare%20workers%20have%20continued%20in%20the%20years%20and%20of%20course%2C%20attacks%20against%20healthcare%20facilities%20were%20already%20illegal%20under%20the%20Geneva%20conventions%20%5Bbefore%20the%20UN%20resolution%20came%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20we%20have%20a%20long%20history%20here%2C%20of%20acts%20that%20have%20already%20been%20declared%20as%20a%20breach%20of%20international%20humanitarian%20law%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20such%20violence%2C%C2%A0%20acts%20are%20committed%20nevertheless.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20an%20elected%20government%2C%20which%20is%20a%20party%20to%20the%20UN%20resolution%2C%20attacks%20the%20healthcare%20facilities%2C%20it%20creates%20a%20conflicting%20situation.%20In%20other%20conflicts%2C%20there%20are%20typically%20two%20groups%2C%20most%20probably%20militia%20groups%2C%20fighting%20against%20each%20other%20and%20attacking%20the%20healthcare%20facilities.%20Do%20you%20believe%20that%20such%20disparity%20exists%20in%20the%20current%20conflict%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20it%20holds%20significance%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20scale%20of%20aggression%20is%20important%20here.%20I%20mean%20the%20one%20thing%20that%20I%20would%20say%2C%20as%20a%20healthcare%20worker%2C%20is%20that%20attacks%20against%20healthcare%20facilities%20and%20health%20workers%20are%20a%20horrific%20breach%20of%20international%20humanitarian%20law%20and%20they%20are%20not%20permitted%20under%20any%20circumstance%20in%20any%20conflict%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20a%20discussion%20about%20who%20is%20the%20perpetrator%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20important%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20pursuit%20of%20accountability%20and%20justice%2C%20people%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20afforded%20impunity%20whoever%20the%20perpetrator%20may%20be.%20But%20for%20me%20what%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20is%20that%20we%20must%20reiterate%20and%20we%20must%20ensure%20adequate%20protection%20for%20our%20healthcare%20worker%20colleagues%20wherever%20they%E2%80%99re%20practising%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20believe%C2%A0%20there%20were%20attacks%20on%20healthcare%20facilities%20in%20the%20past%20and%20there%20was%20not%20enough%20reaction%20against%20those%20attacks%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20this%2C%20sort%20of%2C%20empowered%20an%20elected%20government%20to%20go%20against%20these%20facilities%20with%20complete%20impunity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20I%20mean%20if%20we%20see%20in%20situations%20where%20there%20is%20a%20complete%20lack%20of%20accountability%20for%20such%20attacks%2C%20you%20can%20imagine%20then%20that%20parties%20to%20a%20conflict%20will%20act%20with%20impunity%20because%20they%20know%20that%20they%20can%20get%20away%20with%20these%20violations%20of%20international%20law.%20And%20again%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20say%20this%20in%20specific%20reference%20to%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%20This%20is%20a%20global%20problem%20and%20it%20should%20be%20a%20concern%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20can%20say%20a%20lot%20about%20governments%20and%20how%20they%20reacted%20to%20this%20conflict%2C%20but%20do%20you%20also%20believe%20that%20the%20reaction%20that%20should%20have%20come%20from%20the%20healthcare%20community%2C%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20against%20these%20horrific%20ongoing%20attacks%2C%20was%20also%20not%20enough%3F%20Why%20do%20you%20think%20that%20all%20doctors%2C%20nurses%20and%20all%20healthcare%20workers%20could%20not%20come%20out%20in%20one%20single%20voice%20saying%20that%20we%20need%20to%20stop%20these%20attacks%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20would%20say%20there%20have%20been%20some%20strong%20statements%2C%20there%20have%20been%20some%20health%20justice%20organisations%20that%20have%20issued%20statements%20calling%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20violence%2C%20calling%20for%20meaningful%20investment%20in%20pathways%20towards%20peace%20and%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20there%20have%20been%20some%20calls%20but%20I%20would%20agree%20that%20they%20have%20not%20been%20coordinated%20or%20strong%20or%20particularly%20present%20globally.%20It%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20know%20why%20folks%2C%20for%20example%2C%20in%20the%20UK%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20this%20as%20a%20shared%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20would%20argue%20as%20a%20healthcare%20worker%2C%20as%20someone%20who%20has%20studied%2C%20taught%20and%20practised%20humanitarianism%2C%20that%20we%20should%20recognise%20what%20unites%20us%20all%20and%20when%20we%20see%20situations%20such%20as%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20now%20in%20Gaza%2C%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20in%20Israel%2C%20we%20need%20to%20be%20unified%20in%20horror%2C%20but%20we%20also%20need%20to%20be%20unified%20in%20a%20commitment%20to%20doing%20something%20about%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%5BWe%20need%5D%20to%20speak%20up%20in%20pursuit%20of%20an%20end%20to%20the%20violence%2C%20and%20justice%20and%20peace%2C%20over%20the%20longer%20term%2C%20I%20do%20feel%20that.%20That%20is%20a%20strong%20responsibility%20of%20healthcare%20workers%20that%20is%20rooted%20in%20our%20professional%20commitments%20to%20care%2C%20not%20only%20to%20our%20patients%20but%20also%20to%20care%20for%20our%20community%20and%20in%20the%20very%20broadest%20sense%2C%20the%20global%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWere%20you%20able%20to%20speak%20to%20any%20of%20your%20colleagues%20working%20in%20Gaza%20at%20this%20point%20in%20time%3F%20Could%20you%20describe%20the%20mental%20well-being%20of%20healthcare%20workers%20there%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20for%20this%20question.%20I%20think%20it%20is%20really%20important%20that%20we%20amplify%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20hearing%20from%20healthcare%20workers%20inside%20Gaza%2C%20inside%20Palestine.I%20get%20a%20few%20messages%20from%20the%20folks%20directly%2C%20but%20I%20also%20hear%20a%20lot%20through%20secondary%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20%5Banswer%5D%20your%20question%20about%20the%20sort%20of%20psychological%20toll%20that%20this%20ongoing%20violence%20is%20having%20on%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%20unimaginable%2C%20even%20for%20those%20of%20us%20who%E2%80%99ve%20worked%20in%20conflict%20settings.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20unimaginable%20to%20fathom%20what%20our%20colleagues%20in%20Gaza%20must%20be%20going%20through%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20see%20a%20progressive%20increase%20in%20the%20intensity%20of%20violence%2C%20in%20the%20intensity%20of%20bombardments.%20We%20have%20colleagues%20who%E2%80%99ve%20now%20been%20working%20almost%20non-stop%20since%20October%207%2C%20providing%20surgical%20and%20emergency%20care%2C%20and%20ensuring%20to%20the%20best%20extent%20that%20is%20possible.%20Their%20ability%20to%20maintain%20the%20continuity%20of%20existing%20services%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20important%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20providing%20trauma%20care%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20expectant%20mothers%20in%20Gaza.%20There%20are%20individuals%20who%20have%20been%20receiving%20radiotherapy%20and%20chemotherapy%20for%20cancers.%20And%20there%20are%20ongoing%20specialist%20service%20provision%20for%20children.%20All%20of%20these%20services%20have%20been%20disrupted%20to%20a%20phenomenal%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20colleagues%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20do%20the%20best%20of%20their%20ability%20to%20maintain%20some%20degree%20of%20service%20provision%20while%20also%20responding%20to%20the%20acute%20conflict-related%20needs%20and%20the%20psychological%20impact.%20They%20are%20working%20almost%20non-stop%2C%20with%20minimal%20sleep%2C%20not%20eating%20well%2C%20not%20sleeping%20well%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20%5BWe%20are%5D%20seeing%20and%20experiencing%20the%20horrific%20consequences%20of%20violence%20that%20will%20leave%20a%20major%20psychological%20toll%20on%20our%20colleagues%20working%20in%20Gaza%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20governments%20have%20done%20what%20they%20could%20have%20done%20or%20not%20done%2C%20what%20they%20were%20capable%20of.%20But%20what%20do%20you%20expect%20from%20them%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20need%20most%20immediately%2C%20Banjot%2C%20is%20an%20end%20to%20the%20violence.%20So%20the%20call%20right%20now%20is%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire.%20Let%20us%20make%20sure%20that%20this%20situation%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20get%20worse%20than%20it%20already%20is.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20we%20have%20to%20see%20a%20situation%20in%20which%20there%20is%20a%20serious%20meaningful%20investment%20in%20a%20peace%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fde-escalation-ceasefire-among-phrases-to-avoid-in-press-materials-show-us-state-dept-emails%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98De-escalation%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Ceasefire%E2%80%99%20Among%20Phrases%20to%20Avoid%20in%20Press%20Materials%2C%20Show%20US%20State%20Dept%20Emails%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20has%20been%20criticism%2C%20if%20I%20may%20say%2C%20of%20your%20editorial.%20I%20believe%20some%20letters%20were%20also%20written%20to%20the%20editor-in-chief%20of%20the%20journal.%20Would%20you%20want%20to%20respond%20to%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESure.%20Thank%20you%20for%20this%20question.%20I%20should%20begin%20by%20saying%20that%20while%20there%20has%20been%20criticism%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20received%20several%20compliments%20%5Bas%20well%5D%2C%20as%20open%20letters%20were%20submitted%20to%20the%20journal%20in%20support%20of%20not%20only%20us%20for%20writing%20this%20piece%20but%20also%20of%20the%20%3Ci%3EBMJ%20Global%20Health%3C%2Fi%3E%20for%20publishing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20I%E2%80%99m%20sure%20many%20of%20your%20readers%20have%20seen%2C%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20and%20the%20broader%20situation%20in%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%20is%20an%20incredibly%20polarising%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20individuals%20%5Bdoctors%5D%20took%20issue%20with%20the%20way%20we%20had%20framed%20this%20matter.%20They%20felt%20that%20we%20were%20speaking%20too%20strongly%20about%20the%20violence%20committed%20against%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20%3Ci%3EBMJ%20Global%20Health%3C%2Fi%3E%20editorial%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20a%20knowledge%20vacuum.%20We%20know%20that%20many%20major%20mainstream%20media%20outlets%20are%20reporting%20on%20the%20violence%20in%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%20right%20now%2C%20many%20have%20spoken%20about%20the%20horrific%20atrocities%20that%20were%20committed%20on%20October%207%20against%20Israeli%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20do%20acknowledge%20the%20%5Bviolence%20against%20Israeli%20citizens%5D%20in%20the%20introduction%20to%20this%20editorial%2C%20some%20folks%20felt%20that%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20speak%20to%20that%20in%20the%20way%20that%20we%20should%20have%20done%2C%20and%20I%20say%20in%20response%20to%20that%20as%20I%E2%80%99ve%20said%20this%20editorial%20exists%20within%20that%20wide%20knowledge%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20recognise%20that%20many%20outlets%20are%20speaking%20about%20these%20very%20important%20issues%2C%20particularly%20the%20events%20that%20took%20place%20on%20October%207%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20700%20Israeli%20hostages%20who%20are%20still%20being%20held%20captive%20inside%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20folks%2C%20as%20you%E2%80%99ve%20alluded%20to%20in%20some%20of%20your%20earlier%20questions%2C%20aren%E2%80%99t%20happy%20with%20this%20sort%20of%20blurring%20between%20the%20medical%20and%20healthcare%20professions%20and%20political%20positioning.%20But%2C%20as%20I%E2%80%99ve%20said%20already%2C%20I%20think%20that%20we%20need%20to%20recognise%20that%20medicine%20is%20political%2C%20healthcare%20is%20political%2C%20and%20we%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20shy%20away%20from%20navigating%20the%20complex%20and%20messy%20world%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699448427000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04114430%2Fal-shifa.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-political-medical-community-israel-gaza-conflict%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22James%20Smith%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20t