k-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Focus%20on%20what%20you%20know%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F281037%2Fhow-to-crack-upsc-interview-tips-ias-officer-twitter-personality-test%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJitin%20Yadav%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%202016-batch%20IAS%20officer%2C%20says%20that%20having%20confidence%20in%20what%20you%20already%20know%20is%20more%20important%20than%20worrying%20about%20what%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDo%20not%20feel%20underconfident%20imagining%20how%20much%20you%20do%20not%20know.%20Focus%20on%20gaining%20confidence%20from%20how%20much%20you%20already%20know.%20If%20you%20are%20a%20serious%20aspirant%2C%20then%20that%20is%20more%20than%20enough%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E15%20Golden%20Tips%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FUPSC%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23UPSC%3C%2Fa%3E%20Civil%20Services%20Examination%20Personality%20Test%2FInterview%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%231%20Always%20allow%20the%20interview%20board%20member%20to%20interrupt%20you%20but%20never%20interrupt%20the%20board%20member.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%232%20Answer%20one%20question%20at%20a%20time.%20Never%20mix%20the%20previous%20question%20with%20the%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Jitin%20Yadav%20(%40Jitin_IAS)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJitin_IAS%2Fstatus%2F1508890225270951937%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2029%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Learn%20to%20be%20a%20good%20listener%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EJitin%20advises%20aspirants%20to%20be%20good%20listeners%20and%20take%20a%20pause%20before%20replying%20to%20a%20question.%20%E2%80%9CSome%20aspirants%20start%20framing%20their%20answers%20before%20the%20ques